Title: Red, White & Royal Blue
Author: Casey McQuiston
Private Notes: My fav book ever so far! Has everything from politics, British royalty, hidden and secret love and meet-ups, includes sex scenes, diversity in race/sexual orientation, powerful women leaders (mom is president), close friends (sister and friend), friend does modeling for campaign (Nate silver reference), partying and alcohol, late night outings, DC and govt buildings....in love with the whole book!

Title: Lie With Me
Author: Philippe Besson
Private Notes: Very French, format was weird as it didn't have chapters but tons of page breaks (many for no reason/unnecessary), mostly just one man's long thought of about a high school crush/sexual relationship between two boys, ending isn't as powerful as I wanted or could have been, ends with the author meeting lover's son and the son saying his father died by suicide and left a letter intended for author saying at the end of high school they were better apart and author was destined for greatness and to leave
